{{see|eve}}

==English==

===Etymology===
Greek (Eva), from Hebrew [[חווה]] (hawa) = 'life; lively; giving life'. Another translation of Hevrew Hava into Greek: (Zoe), meaning 'life'. Hebrew male equivalent: (Chaim, Haim).

===Proper noun===
'''Eve'''
# according to the [[Bible]] and [[Qur'an]], the first [[woman]] and [[mother]] of the [[human race]]; [[Adam]]'s [[wife]]

